To create File

= touch myfile.txt (create new empty file)

To write text to the file

= echo " Hello , this is my first line" > myfile.txt
 (> means â€œwrite fresh, overwrite anything inside.â€)

To append new lines

= echo "This is my second line" >> myfile.txt
  echo "And here is a third line" >> myfile.txt
  (ðŸ‘‰ >> means add to the file without erasing whatâ€™s already there)

(echo "First line" > myfile.txt
echo "Second line" >> myfile.txt
echo "Third line" >> myfile.txt)

Read the File Back

= cat myfile.txt ( Shows the whole file contents)

Read the Beginning

= head -n 2 myfile.txt

Read the End

= tail -n 2 myfile.txt

Use tee to Write and Display at the Same Time

echo"Line 4 : added with tee " | tee -a myfile.txt
